tentative name parsec or parse c 04/11/2026
Parse master file table written in C

Updates to follow but the structure is complete and tested. Will add more finish to it such as system time currently its UTC which is -7:00 where 
I am. The filesize of the parser is 170kb and it is fairly fast. I chose to write it in C as its perfectly suited for the task and I also needed 
a solution for my Qt application. 

usage:
optional drive (default C:)
./parser.exe
./parser.exe S:
./parser.exe C: --cutoff "2026-03-19 10:13:18"

will output in format:
recordnumber frn parent_frn mtime ctime fileattrib isdir|name|path


optional argument (one max)

search for new files by time (UTC)
--cutoff "2026-03-19 10:13:18" or 2026-03-19T10:13:18

list mft record
--target <recordno>

same as with no optional argument but better format for parsing for Qt gui
will output in format:
recordnumber|frn|parent_frn|mtime|ctime|fileattrib|isdir|name|path
--parse

